This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and language identification. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the authors mention the use of a lexical baseline system. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves the development of a dataset for a specific task. The use of annotation and parsing techniques suggests that it could also be classified under cs.RO (Robotics) as these techniques are often used in robotics research. Finally, the paper's focus on educational NLP suggests that it could be categorized under cs.ED (Education).
